        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "**Column of nude figures.** A vertical column of small nude women is drawn inside a blue-leafed canopy, descending toward a green basin or root. The motif of stacked nymphs occurs across the manuscript's balneological / biological quires; readers have variously read this as embryology, allegorical alchemy, or a generative diagram of bodily fluids — nothing has stuck.",
